comments.body:
@QiWang19 My general comment here is that we should be able to do this function without adding multiple endpoints, specifically, to the varlink API. 

For example, there should be a Copy endpoint.  When the remote client connects to the endpoint, it should call into the copy endpoint.  that endpoint, depending on how you set this up, should call a libpod API for Copy or at worst several APIs.  The reason you want less calls is so you don't have to duplicate this for the local client calls.

there are already calls for sending and receiving files through varlink. see export, import, save, load for examples of that and I can of course help.
